article.headline: Campbell 77, Iowa 61
article.story: IOWA CITY, Iowa -- Eric Griffin had 23 points and 13 rebounds as Campbell defeated Iowa 77-61 on Wednesday night. The Fighting Camels are 5-0 for the first time since 1976 after shooting 62 percent from the field. Iowa (3-2) trailed by as many as 16 points and cut the deficit to 54-49 with 10 minutes left. But the Hawkeyes couldn't get any closer despite forcing 22 turnovers. Darren White scored 17 points for Campbell, which blocked 10 shots. Trey Freeman added 15 points. Matt Gatens led Iowa with 17 points. Devyn Marble added 14 points.
